[normal]Case Study[bold] 2[bold]: [bold]Major event, [bold]Women’s Rugby World Cup[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]In 2010 England hosted the Women’s Rugby World Cup.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]  The competition was contested over 16 days with 30 matches between 12 nations. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Interest in the tournament was far higher 
[normal]than in the previous five WRWCs.  Thirteen matches were broadcast live by Sky Sports to 127 countries and all pool games were sold out with a total attendance of 30,000 over the tournament.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The final was held at the Twickenham Stoop with England 
[normal]finishing
[normal] as runner up
[normal].  
[normal]It
[normal] was attended by a 
[normal]world 
[normal]record crowd for the wo
[normal]men’s 
[normal]15
[normal]s game of around 13,500, and saw a TV audience of half a million.
