[normal]Fan engagement[bold]4.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The RFU has recently undertaken research on fans so we can better understand our customers with a view to making their experience better, and 
[normal]to widen
[normal] access to rugby to attract those who don’t currently come to Twickenham.  M
[normal]atches at Twickenham attract a
[normal] surprisingly high proportion of women
[normal] 
[normal]compared to similar sport
[normal]s
[normal] with approximately 35% attendees at rugby matches at Twickenham being female.  For th
[normal]e 
[normal]Marriott London Sevens
[normal] weekend the 
[normal]attendees are equally split between male and female
[normal], due to the youn
[normal]ger profile of the audience and the relaxed atmosphere of this particular event.  The RFU will be 
[normal]analysing
[normal] these results and working with focus groups 
[normal]to find out why there is such a gulf between the n
[normal]umber of women who claim to be “passionate about rugby
[normal]”
[normal], and the numbers that are motivated to participate in the Game.
