[normal]Case Study 4[bold]: ER2015 CEO, Debbie Jevans CBE[bold]Debbie Jevans joined England Rugby 2015 as Chief Executive in October 2012.  Debbie is the first female ever to be appointed as Chief Executive 
[normal]of a Rugby World Cup. Leading the Rugby World Cup 2015 Tournament Organising Committee, Jevans
[normal] 
[normal]and her team will deliver the third largest global sporting event, hosted in England between September 18 and October 31 2015. Preparations for the Tournament; w
[normal]hich will see 48 games played across the breadth of the country, with attendances of over 2 million and an excess of 500,000 spectators travelling into England, are well underway.  
[normal]Previously Director of Sport for LOCOG, Jevans was part of arguably the mo
[normal]st successful Olympic and Paralympic Games in history.  Previously she ran her own sport consultancy firm working with clients such as the International Tennis Federation (ITF), BBC, the International Rugby Board (IRB), International Cricket Council (ICC) 
[normal]and UK Sport.  Debbie is also a member of the All England Lawn Tennis Club’s Committee of Management and Championships Committee and sits on the UK Sport Major Events Panel.
[normal]&#xa0;
