[normal]Case Study 6: RFU Council Member, Deborah Griffin OBE[bold] 
[normal]Deborah started playing rugby at University C
[normal]ollege London and was a founding member of the WRFU in 1983 and chaired the organisation of the first Women’s Rugby World Cup in Cardiff in 1991.
[normal] 
[normal]Deborah captained the first English women’s club side at Finchley in its first year and later at Richmond.  R
[normal]eturning as Finance Officer to the RFUW in 2002 and subsequently Chair of the Board, Deborah saw 
[normal]the
[normal] RFUW to full integration in 2012.  She is also a Bursar at Homerton College, Cambridge University.
[normal]  
[normal]Deborah was awarded the OBE for services to women’s ru
[normal]gby in 2011 in recognition of her role in establishing the England women’s side and the women’s World Cup.
[normal]Case Study [bold]7[bold]: [bold]RFU Council Member, [bold]Tracy Edmundson[bold] 
[normal]Tracy Edmundson was the first female to be elected as a Rugby Football Union Council Member in June 2013.  She is one of two Council representatives for 
[normal]Notts, Lincs &amp; Derbyshire.
[normal]Tracy was an active member of Derby RFC since 2002 and holds a number of key
[normal] voluntary roles in the club.  She previously worked in advertising and marketing and still works for a management consultancy which 
[normal]specialises
[normal] in procurement, energy and management systems.
